742
00:50:38,210 --> 00:50:41,210
...one of Hudsucker's largest
and most loyal stockholders.

743
00:50:41,290 --> 00:50:43,610
What's this I hear
about you being an imbecile?

744
00:50:43,690 --> 00:50:45,250
What's ailing you, boy?

745
00:50:45,410 --> 00:50:49,370
Last week, my stock was worth twice
what it is now. I think I'll sell...

746
00:50:49,450 --> 00:50:53,330
...the whole kit and caboodle, boy,
unless I see a vast improvement.

747
00:50:53,690 --> 00:50:56,180
What you've got here, son, is a range war!

748
00:50:56,340 --> 00:51:00,060
You gonna have to circle our wagons
or I'm gonna get out of your wagon train.

749
00:51:01,580 --> 00:51:03,660
No need for concern, sir.
It's only natural...

750
00:51:03,780 --> 00:51:06,860
...in a period of transition for the more
timid elements to run for cover.

751
00:51:06,900 --> 00:51:09,820
Yellow? I'll show you yellow, boy!

752
00:51:10,540 --> 00:51:13,420
You mind now and quit acting
like such an old grizzly.

753
00:51:13,620 --> 00:51:15,420
Step lively here, Norville.

754
00:51:15,940 --> 00:51:19,020
I'm sorry, I thought maybe if I showed him
the long view...

755
00:51:19,260 --> 00:51:21,940
And this is Thorstensen Finlandson...

756
00:51:22,180 --> 00:51:24,820
...who heads a radical, splinter group
of disgruntled investors.

757
00:51:24,900 --> 00:51:26,260
Pleased to meet you.

758
00:51:26,340 --> 00:51:29,740
It might interest you to know I studied
a little Finnish in high school.

759
00:51:29,780 --> 00:51:31,380
I hope I'm not too rusty.

760
00:51:38,820 --> 00:51:42,220
Ladies and gentlemen, distinguished
members of the Hudsucker Board...

761
00:51:42,260 --> 00:51:46,340
...I give you the Rajah of Romance,
the Ministereo of Moonlight...

762
00:51:46,700 --> 00:51:48,980
...the incredible, the unforgettable...

763
00:51:49,060 --> 00:51:51,860
...Mr. Vic Tenetta!

764
00:51:58,350 --> 00:51:59,990
"Rajah". I like that.

765
00:52:41,310 --> 00:52:42,670
What happened?

766
00:52:44,030 --> 00:52:48,350
Nothing. Just the more timid investors
are no longer running for cover.

767
00:52:48,510 --> 00:52:49,590
Let me look.

768
00:52:50,190 --> 00:52:51,510
Sid found me the ice pack.

769
00:52:51,550 --> 00:52:54,150
Let me hold it or you'll have a real shiner.

770
00:52:55,510 --> 00:52:58,160
I guess people are pretty hot
over this imbecile story.

771
00:52:58,760 --> 00:53:00,040
I'm sorry.

772
00:53:00,720 --> 00:53:04,520
It's not your fault. You've the one person
standing by me through all this.

773
00:53:04,600 --> 00:53:07,280
Norville, there's something
I have to tell you.

774
00:53:08,200 --> 00:53:09,240
You see...

775
00:53:09,880 --> 00:53:11,760
...I'm not really a secretary.

776
00:53:12,680 --> 00:53:13,800
I know that, Amy.

777
00:53:13,880 --> 00:53:14,840
You do?

778
00:53:15,040 --> 00:53:18,040
I understand you're not very skilled yet
in the secretarial arts...

779
00:53:18,120 --> 00:53:21,120
...but I'll tell you a secret:
I'm not that skilled as president.

780
00:53:21,160 --> 00:53:24,480
-I know I put up a big front, but...
-I believe in you, Norville.

781
00:53:26,080 --> 00:53:27,120
At least...

782
00:53:27,640 --> 00:53:29,960
...I believe in your intentions.

783
00:53:30,200 --> 00:53:33,520
I don't blame them, really.
I suppose I have made a mess of things.

784
00:53:34,120 --> 00:53:36,320
Those folks have to protect
their investment.

785
00:53:36,360 --> 00:53:37,920
Most of them are very nice people.

786
00:53:37,960 --> 00:53:41,280
Listen, you can't trust people here
like you did in Muncie.

787
00:53:41,320 --> 00:53:43,320
Certain people are...

788
00:53:43,400 --> 00:53:47,200
Did you ever go to the top of Larson's
feed tower and look out over the town?

789
00:53:48,120 --> 00:53:49,440
On Farm Route 17?

790
00:53:49,800 --> 00:53:52,160
Oh, yes, in Muncie.

791
00:53:53,320 --> 00:53:55,880
No, Vidalia. Farm Route 17.

792
00:53:57,530 --> 00:54:00,810
Seventeen. Yes, I....
Well, no, no. I never really...

793
00:54:02,530 --> 00:54:06,130
The guys from the Varsity Squad
would bring their dates up there...

794
00:54:07,170 --> 00:54:08,450
...to hold hands.

795
00:54:09,250 --> 00:54:11,410
Of course, I never made Varsity.

796
00:54:13,970 --> 00:54:15,730
There's a place I go now.

797
00:54:16,530 --> 00:54:19,450
Cutest little place near my apartment
in Greenwich Village.

798
00:54:19,530 --> 00:54:21,410
It's called "Ann's 440".

799
00:54:21,730 --> 00:54:23,090
It's a beatnik bar.

800
00:54:23,170 --> 00:54:24,530
-You don't say?
-Yes.

801
00:54:24,610 --> 00:54:25,570
A beatnik bar.

802
00:54:25,650 --> 00:54:29,010
You can get carrot juice or ltalian coffee
and the people there...

803
00:54:29,610 --> 00:54:31,250
Well, none of them quite fit in.

804
00:54:31,850 --> 00:54:33,010
You'd love it.

805
00:54:33,490 --> 00:54:34,890
Come there with me.

806
00:54:35,370 --> 00:54:38,130
There's a marathon poetry-reading
on New Year's Eve. I go every year.

807
00:54:38,170 --> 00:54:40,370
-It's marvelous!
-Every year?

808
00:54:42,450 --> 00:54:46,690
Well, this year, if it's good,
I plan to make it a tradition.

809
00:54:48,850 --> 00:54:50,730
My, it certainly is beautiful.

810
00:54:51,490 --> 00:54:52,970
The people...

811
00:54:53,410 --> 00:54:54,890
...look like ants.

812
00:54:56,010 --> 00:54:59,060
The Hindus, and the beatniks also,
say that...

813
00:54:59,580 --> 00:55:02,260
...in our next lives some of us
will come back as ants.

814
00:55:02,700 --> 00:55:06,700
Some will be butterflies, others will be
elephants or creatures of the sea.

815
00:55:06,860 --> 00:55:08,260
What a beautiful thought.

816
00:55:08,420 --> 00:55:11,020
What do you think you were
in a previous life?

817
00:55:12,060 --> 00:55:13,620
Oh, I don't know.

818
00:55:14,380 --> 00:55:15,820
Maybe I was just...

819
00:55:16,220 --> 00:55:20,180
...a fast-talking career gal
who thought she was one of the boys.

820
00:55:20,300 --> 00:55:21,420
Oh, no, Amy.

821
00:55:21,660 --> 00:55:24,420
Pardon me for saying so,
but I find that very far-fetched.

822
00:55:24,540 --> 00:55:28,380
-There really is something I must tell you.
-That person would come back as a hog.

823
00:55:28,460 --> 00:55:31,060
I find it more likely that you were...

824
00:55:32,380 --> 00:55:33,380
...a gazelle...

825
00:55:34,300 --> 00:55:37,780
...with long, graceful legs,
gamboling through the underbrush.

826
00:55:38,620 --> 00:55:40,180
Perhaps we met once.

827
00:55:40,860 --> 00:55:43,460
A chance encounter in a forest glade.

828
00:55:45,340 --> 00:55:47,780
I must have been an antelope or an ibex.

829
00:55:48,940 --> 00:55:52,340
The times we must've had
foraging together for sustenance...

830
00:55:53,260 --> 00:55:55,740
...snorfling water
from a mountain stream...

831
00:55:56,300 --> 00:55:59,750
...picking the grubs and burrs
from one another's coats.

832
00:56:02,390 --> 00:56:06,750
Or perhaps we simply touched horns
briefly and went our separate ways.

833
00:56:08,030 --> 00:56:10,550
Oh, I wish it were that simple, Norville.

834
00:56:11,910 --> 00:56:15,950
I wish I was still a gazelle
and you were an antelope...

835
00:56:16,790 --> 00:56:18,070
...or an ibex.

836
00:56:22,470 --> 00:56:24,030
Can I at least call you...

837
00:56:24,350 --> 00:56:25,350
...deer?

838
00:56:28,390 --> 00:56:29,470
You're funny.

839
00:56:29,510 --> 00:56:32,670
Seriously, Amy, it's what
your beatnik friends call "karma".

840
00:56:32,870 --> 00:56:33,670
Karma.

841
00:56:33,750 --> 00:56:36,590
The great circle of life, death and rebirth.

842
00:56:36,750 --> 00:56:40,310
I think I heard of that.
What goes around comes around.

843
00:56:40,390 --> 00:56:43,790
That's it. A great wheel
that gives us all what we deserve.

844
00:56:45,110 --> 00:56:48,190
I've go to show Sid and all the guys
I deserve their confidence.

845
00:56:48,270 --> 00:56:50,630
Tomorrow's my big presentation
to the board.

846
00:56:53,030 --> 00:56:54,230
Kiss me, Amy!

847
00:56:54,590 --> 00:56:56,070
Kiss me once for luck.

848
00:56:57,430 --> 00:56:58,630
Sure, Norville.

849
00:57:38,400 --> 00:57:39,720
You know, for kids!

850
00:57:40,000 --> 00:57:43,720
It has economy, simplicity, low
production cost, potential for mass appeal.

851
00:57:43,760 --> 00:57:46,000
All that spells out great profitability.

852
00:57:46,040 --> 00:57:48,680
I had the boys at R&D
make this prototype...

853
00:57:48,720 --> 00:57:50,640
...so our discussion
could have some focus...

854
00:57:50,680 --> 00:57:54,440
...and to give you gentleman a firsthand
look at how exciting this gizmo is.

855
00:57:54,480 --> 00:57:57,760
It's fun, healthy, good exercise,
and the kids'll love it.

856
00:57:57,880 --> 00:58:00,840
We put a little sand inside
to make the experience more pleasant.

857
00:58:00,880 --> 00:58:04,090
The great part is we don't have
to charge an arm and a leg.

858
00:58:06,650 --> 00:58:09,370
-What if you tire before it's done?
-Does it have rules?

859
00:58:09,450 --> 00:58:11,530
-Can more than one play?
-Why is it a game?

860
00:58:11,610 --> 00:58:13,130
-Is it a game?
-Will it break?

861
00:58:13,210 --> 00:58:15,290
-It better break eventually.
-Is there an object?

862
00:58:15,370 --> 00:58:17,930
-What if you tire before it's done?
-Does it have batteries?

863
00:58:18,010 --> 00:58:20,730
-Could we charge extra for them?
-Is it safe for toddlers?

864
00:58:20,810 --> 00:58:23,130
-How do you know you're finished?
-How does it stop?

865
00:58:23,170 --> 00:58:25,690
-Is that a boy's model?
-Can a parent assemble it?

866
00:58:25,810 --> 00:58:29,850
-What if you tire before it's done?
-Is there a larger model for the obese?

867
00:58:29,930 --> 00:58:32,050
What the hell is it?

868
00:58:32,090 --> 00:58:33,370
Well, it's....

869
00:58:37,050 --> 00:58:38,090
Brilliant!

870
00:58:39,930 --> 00:58:40,970
Genius.

871
00:58:42,010 --> 00:58:45,370
It's exactly what Hudsucker Industry needs
at this juncture.

872
00:58:46,250 --> 00:58:50,530
Even a blind man can tell you
there'll be an enormous demand for this...

873
00:58:51,930 --> 00:58:52,970
...this....

874
00:58:53,850 --> 00:58:54,850
Congratulations.

875
00:58:54,930 --> 00:58:57,330
You've outdone yourself.
You've reinvented the wheel.

876
00:58:57,410 --> 00:59:00,250
I'll recommend to the board
that we proceed immediately...

877
00:59:01,890 --> 00:59:03,220
...and that the...

878
00:59:04,900 --> 00:59:07,500
...dingus be mass-produced
with all deliberate speed.

879
00:59:07,900 --> 00:59:09,580
Although, you realize...

880
00:59:10,020 --> 00:59:11,260
...of course...

881
00:59:14,340 --> 00:59:15,620
...as president...

882
00:59:15,940 --> 00:59:17,860
...the ultimate decision is yours.

883
00:59:19,020 --> 00:59:20,220
I'm for it.

884
01:00:06,990 --> 01:00:08,270
The Flying Doughnut!

885
01:00:08,310 --> 01:00:10,590
-The Dancing Dingus!
-The Belly-Go-Round.

886
01:00:10,670 --> 01:00:11,870
The Swingerina!

887
01:00:11,950 --> 01:00:13,350
The Wacky Circumference!

888
01:00:13,390 --> 01:00:15,150
Uncle Midriff!

889
01:00:44,710 --> 01:00:46,430
-We need something short!
-Sharp!

890
01:00:46,510 --> 01:00:47,190
Snappy!

891
01:00:47,270 --> 01:00:49,630
-With a little jazz!
-The Shazzammeter!

892
01:00:49,710 --> 01:00:51,830
-The Hipster!
-The Daddy-O!

893
01:01:31,440 --> 01:01:33,040
-The Hoopsucker.
-The Hudswinger.

894
01:01:33,120 --> 01:01:35,280
-The Hoopsucker!
-The Hudswinger!

895
01:01:35,320 --> 01:01:37,000
-The Hoopsucker!
-The Hudswinger!

896
01:02:03,960 --> 01:02:06,010
-Fellas!
-You got something?

897
01:02:07,650 --> 01:02:09,370
I got something!

898
01:05:13,640 --> 01:05:17,640
Rockwell News presents: Tidbits of Time.

899
01:05:18,000 --> 01:05:20,600
World news in pictures, we kid you not!

900
01:05:20,960 --> 01:05:24,080
As Old Man 1958 hobbles
towards his finish...

901
01:05:24,640 --> 01:05:26,960
...Barnes is the name
on every American lip.

902
01:05:27,120 --> 01:05:30,520
Norville Barnes, young president
of Hudsucker Industries...

903
01:05:30,560 --> 01:05:34,080
...a boy bred in the heartland,
but now the toast of New York.

904
01:05:34,560 --> 01:05:38,880
Barnes is the brainy inventor of America's
craziest craze: The Hula Hoop!

905
01:05:39,400 --> 01:05:42,960
Reaping huge profits for his company
and winning the hearts...

906
01:05:43,240 --> 01:05:45,680
...and hips of every youngster in America!

907
01:05:47,080 --> 01:05:48,480
Did I say youngster?

908
01:05:48,720 --> 01:05:51,600
Here's Mom taking a break
from her household chores...

909
01:05:52,320 --> 01:05:54,680
...and even Dad is swinging into the act!

910
01:05:56,240 --> 01:06:00,840
Cards, letters, congratulations come
pouring in from Kankakee to Petaluma...

911
01:06:01,200 --> 01:06:04,280
...including one very special
long-distance call.

912
01:06:04,520 --> 01:06:06,400
He's on! He's on the line!

913
01:06:12,810 --> 01:06:15,010
Hello, Norville. This is the President.

914
01:06:15,450 --> 01:06:18,810
I just wanted to congratulate you.
I'm very proud of you.

915
01:06:19,410 --> 01:06:21,690
Mrs. Eisenhower is very proud of you.

916
01:06:22,050 --> 01:06:24,490
The American people are very proud of you.

917
01:06:31,290 --> 01:06:34,170
How'd you come up with the idea
for the Hula Hoop?

918
01:06:34,530 --> 01:06:36,370
It was no great idea, really.

919
01:06:36,490 --> 01:06:40,090
A thing like this takes a whole company
to put together. I'm grateful.

920
01:06:40,370 --> 01:06:43,170
Did you have any idea
there'd be such a huge response?

921
01:06:43,210 --> 01:06:46,210
Frankly, I don't think anybody
expected this much hoopla.

922
01:06:48,010 --> 01:06:51,330
"Hoopla on the Hula Hoop".
Can we quote you on that, Mr. Barnes?

923
01:06:51,450 --> 01:06:52,810
Sure, I guess.

924
01:06:53,490 --> 01:06:55,770
Will you give yourself a nice, fat raise?

925
01:06:56,970 --> 01:06:58,130
Come on, you guys.

926
01:07:05,450 --> 01:07:10,020
What scientific principle explains
the motion of this wheel of wonder?

927
01:07:10,100 --> 01:07:12,140
The dingus is quite simple, really.

928
01:07:12,420 --> 01:07:16,420
It operates on the same principles that
keep the earth spinning around the sun...

929
01:07:16,500 --> 01:07:20,780
...and that keeps you from flying off
the earth into the cold reaches of space...

930
01:07:20,900 --> 01:07:23,340
...where you would die
like a miserable Schwein.

931
01:07:23,380 --> 01:07:25,420
Yes, the principle is the same...

932
01:07:25,860 --> 01:07:29,900
...except for the piece of grit
they put in to make the experience...

933
01:07:30,620 --> 01:07:31,740
...more pleasant.

934
01:07:31,820 --> 01:07:34,420
Yes, it's hula-hula everywhere!

935
01:07:34,500 --> 01:07:37,140
From the parties of the Park Avenue
smart set...

936
01:07:40,180 --> 01:07:43,700
...to sweethearts who want
to be married in the swing of things.

937
01:07:47,900 --> 01:07:51,140
Did the board consider you an "Idea Man"
when they promoted you?

938
01:07:51,220 --> 01:07:54,620
I guess. I don't think they promoted me
because they thought I was a schmo.

939
01:07:54,700 --> 01:07:57,860
What's the next big idea for you
and Hudsucker Industries?

940
01:07:57,940 --> 01:08:01,180
I don't know. An idea like this sweet baby
doesn't just come overnight.

941
01:08:01,260 --> 01:08:05,340
Although, I'll tell you one thing:
I certainly didn't expect all this hoopla.

942
01:08:06,100 --> 01:08:07,620
You can quote me on that.

943
01:08:14,950 --> 01:08:18,030
Rumpus Magazine has called you
the most eligible bachelor of the year.

944
01:08:18,110 --> 01:08:21,110
And society pages have been linking you
with fashion model Za-Za.

945
01:08:21,150 --> 01:08:25,030
There's no truth to the rumors.
We're just dear friends. Isn't that right?

946
01:08:31,910 --> 01:08:35,990
How do you respond to the charges that
you're out of ideas? Have you run dry?

947
01:08:36,150 --> 01:08:39,950
Not at all. Just this week I came up
with several new sweet ideas.

948
01:08:40,310 --> 01:08:44,550
A larger model Hula Hoop for the portly,
a battery option for the lazy or spastic.

949
01:08:44,670 --> 01:08:46,950
A model with extra sand
for the hard-of-hearing.

950
01:08:47,030 --> 01:08:48,630
I'm earning my keep.

951
01:08:48,670 --> 01:08:51,230
Speaking of that,
do you expect to get a raise?

952
01:08:51,550 --> 01:08:55,430
By anyone's account I single-handedly
have saved Hudsucker Industries.

953
01:08:55,550 --> 01:08:59,950
Our stock is worth more now than ever.
Yes, I expect to be compensated for that.

954
01:09:19,040 --> 01:09:20,760
Pull yourself together, man.

955
01:09:20,840 --> 01:09:22,240
Nobody told me!

956
01:09:23,160 --> 01:09:25,320
You sold all our stock?

957
01:09:25,760 --> 01:09:27,280
We dumped the whole load.

958
01:09:27,360 --> 01:09:29,640
I had 20,000 shares!

959
01:09:30,320 --> 01:09:31,960
I'd be a millionaire now!

960
01:09:32,040 --> 01:09:34,040
Sure. We'd all be millionaires.

961
01:09:34,720 --> 01:09:36,720
There's no point in looking back.

962
01:09:37,440 --> 01:09:41,200
At the time, Stillson thought that dumping
our position would panic the market...

963
01:09:41,280 --> 01:09:43,200
...further depress the stock.

964
01:09:43,440 --> 01:09:46,840
Then we could buy it back and more,
of course, once it got cheap.

965
01:09:46,920 --> 01:09:47,840
Cheap?

966
01:09:48,240 --> 01:09:50,080
It's never been more valuable!

967
01:09:51,920 --> 01:09:53,120
And I'm ruined.

968
01:09:53,840 --> 01:09:54,800
Ruined!

969
01:10:01,800 --> 01:10:04,880
I'm getting off this merry-go-round!

970
01:10:14,610 --> 01:10:15,690
Plexiglass.

971
01:10:16,250 --> 01:10:17,930
Had it installed last week.

972
01:10:31,290 --> 01:10:32,930
So, the kid caught a wave.

973
01:10:34,570 --> 01:10:37,930
Right now, he and his dingus are on top.

974
01:10:38,490 --> 01:10:40,170
Well, this too shall pass.

975
01:10:41,050 --> 01:10:44,050
Myrtle J. Mussburger
did not raise her boy to go...

976
01:10:44,570 --> 01:10:47,210
...knock-kneed at the first sign of adversity.

977
01:10:47,250 --> 01:10:50,050
I say, we made this chump,
we can break him!

978
01:10:50,890 --> 01:10:53,570
I say, the higher he climbs,
the harder he drops!

979
01:10:55,370 --> 01:10:56,410
I say, yes...

980
01:10:57,290 --> 01:10:58,890
...the kid has a future...

981
01:11:00,250 --> 01:11:01,450
...and in it...

982
01:11:02,410 --> 01:11:04,330
...I see shame, dishonor...

983
01:11:04,970 --> 01:11:06,690
...ignominy, disgrace.

984
01:11:10,490 --> 01:11:12,650
The music plays, the wheel turns...

985
01:11:13,860 --> 01:11:15,820
...and our spin ain't over yet.

986
01:11:39,540 --> 01:11:41,460
For Pete's sakes, Norville!

987
01:11:41,820 --> 01:11:43,620
Where have you been hiding?

988
01:11:43,780 --> 01:11:46,980
Do you know what those nincompoops
in the boardroom are doing?

989
01:11:47,060 --> 01:11:48,620
I wouldn't call them nincompoops.

990
01:11:48,700 --> 01:11:51,060
They're going to discharge 8%
of the workforce here!

991
01:11:51,140 --> 01:11:53,980
In New York City alone,
that means 1,800 people out of work!

992
01:11:54,060 --> 01:11:56,380
People with wives, children and families!

993
01:11:56,660 --> 01:11:58,740
We're pruning away some of the dead wood.

994
01:11:58,820 --> 01:12:00,820
You mean you know about this?

995
01:12:00,860 --> 01:12:02,380
Know about it? Sure.

996
01:12:02,460 --> 01:12:05,460
You think the board would do anything
without my authorization?

997
01:12:05,540 --> 01:12:06,940
It was my idea.

998
01:12:07,020 --> 01:12:08,300
-Your...
-Sure it was.

999
01:12:08,380 --> 01:12:11,180
We're in a period of transition.
Things have slowed down.

1000
01:12:11,260 --> 01:12:13,940
You're being awfully kind to yourself,
Norville Barnes.

1001
01:12:13,980 --> 01:12:17,310
You've slowed down, sitting up here
not doing a lick of work.

1002
01:12:17,830 --> 01:12:22,510
You haven't come up with an idea since
the Hoop and the reason is plain to see!

1003
01:12:22,590 --> 01:12:24,990
You've forgotten what made your ideas
exciting to you.

1004
01:12:25,070 --> 01:12:27,350
It wasn't for the fame and wealth....

1005
01:12:27,430 --> 01:12:31,110
Would you get out of here?
You too, sisters, move it. Out!

1006
01:12:33,270 --> 01:12:36,310
I've been watching you, even though
you've been trying to avoid me.

1007
01:12:36,470 --> 01:12:37,150
Shut up!

1008
01:12:37,190 --> 01:12:39,430
Don't think I haven't noticed
how you've changed.

1009
01:12:39,470 --> 01:12:41,190
I used to think you were a swell guy.

1010
01:12:41,270 --> 01:12:43,230
To be honest,
I thought you were an imbecile.

1011
01:12:43,630 --> 01:12:44,390
Shut up!

1012
01:12:44,470 --> 01:12:47,910
Then I figured out you were a swell guy.
A little slow maybe, but a swell guy.

1013
01:12:47,990 --> 01:12:51,310
Maybe you're not so slow
but you're not so swell either.

1014
01:12:51,390 --> 01:12:53,510
Looks like you're an imbecile, after all.
Shut up!

1015
01:12:54,190 --> 01:12:57,510
You haven't talked to me for a week
and now I'm going to say my piece.

1016
01:12:57,550 --> 01:12:59,510
Look, I've never been...

1017
01:13:00,430 --> 01:13:02,910
...dumped by a fella before,
and that hurts...

1018
01:13:03,270 --> 01:13:06,030
...but what really hurts is watching you
out-run your soul!

1019
01:13:06,110 --> 01:13:08,390
Chasing after money and ease
and the respect of a board...

1020
01:13:08,470 --> 01:13:10,750
...that wouldn't give you the time of day...

1021
01:13:10,790 --> 01:13:11,750
...if you....

1022
01:13:12,310 --> 01:13:13,670
Worked in a watch factory?

1023
01:13:15,150 --> 01:13:16,480
Shut up! Exactly.

1024
01:13:17,680 --> 01:13:21,080
Norville, don't you remember
how you used to feel about the Hoop?

1025
01:13:21,640 --> 01:13:25,080
You told me you'd bring a smile
to the hips of everyone in America...

1026
01:13:25,160 --> 01:13:27,040
...regardless of race, creed or color.

1027
01:13:27,120 --> 01:13:30,600
Finally, there'd be a thingamajig
that would bring everyone together...

1028
01:13:30,640 --> 01:13:32,880
...even if it kept them apart spatially.

1029
01:13:33,320 --> 01:13:34,360
"You know...

1030
01:13:34,840 --> 01:13:35,840
"...for kids".

1031
01:13:36,680 --> 01:13:37,640
Your words...

1032
01:13:38,680 --> 01:13:39,760
...not mine.

1033
01:13:41,080 --> 01:13:42,680
I used to love Norville Barnes.

1034
01:13:43,720 --> 01:13:45,040
Yes, love him...

1035
01:13:45,720 --> 01:13:49,600
...when he was just a swell kid
with hot ideas who was in over his head.

1036
01:13:50,320 --> 01:13:52,520
Now your head's too big to be in over!

1037
01:13:52,640 --> 01:13:54,480
Consider this my resignation.

1038
01:13:55,720 --> 01:13:57,120
Effective immediately!

1039
01:15:13,890 --> 01:15:15,610
Buddy, buddy.

1040
01:15:16,490 --> 01:15:17,490
Buddy.

1041
01:15:18,380 --> 01:15:19,660
Oh, buddy.

1042
01:15:29,060 --> 01:15:30,340
Buddy. You busy?

1043
01:15:32,100 --> 01:15:35,420
Looks like you nodded off there, buddy.
Say, you got a minute?

1044
01:15:38,860 --> 01:15:40,180
Is this important?

1045
01:15:40,260 --> 01:15:43,420
I think so. It's this little idea
I've been working on.

1046
01:15:43,460 --> 01:15:46,060
You see, I don't intend
to be an elevator boy forever.

1047
01:15:46,140 --> 01:15:47,660
Take a look at this sweet baby!

1048
01:15:47,740 --> 01:15:50,060
Get it? Incredibly convenient, isn't it?

1049
01:15:50,180 --> 01:15:51,660
You know, for drinks?

1050
01:15:51,860 --> 01:15:55,660
This is how it works. It's got these ridges
on the side that give it its whammy.

1051
01:15:55,780 --> 01:15:59,260
You don't have to drink like this.
You can drink like this.

1052
01:15:59,380 --> 01:16:01,580
I call it the "Buzz-Sucker".
You get it, buddy?

1053
01:16:01,660 --> 01:16:05,380
People are dying for this and
we won't have to charge an arm and a leg.

1054
01:16:05,420 --> 01:16:06,620
Wait a minute.

1055
01:16:21,350 --> 01:16:22,310
This...

1056
01:16:25,270 --> 01:16:26,390
...is worthless!

1057
01:16:26,670 --> 01:16:27,750
But, buddy!

1058
01:16:28,070 --> 01:16:30,870
This is the most idiotic thing
I've ever seen in my life.

1059
01:16:30,950 --> 01:16:33,190
Nobody wants a hair-brained product
like this.

1060
01:16:33,230 --> 01:16:34,310
You see, Buzz...

1061
01:16:34,390 --> 01:16:36,390
...it lacks the creative spark...

1062
01:16:36,750 --> 01:16:39,630
...the unalloyed genius
that made something like, say...

1063
01:16:40,430 --> 01:16:42,070
...the Hula Hoop such a success.

1064
01:16:42,150 --> 01:16:44,510
How dare you barge in here
and take up my valuable time!

1065
01:16:44,590 --> 01:16:45,910
I've got a company to run!

1066
01:16:48,150 --> 01:16:50,950
I can't have every deadbeat
on the payroll pestering me...

1067
01:16:50,990 --> 01:16:52,670
...with their idiotic brainwaves.

1068
01:16:52,750 --> 01:16:53,910
I'm sorry, buddy.

1069
01:16:53,990 --> 01:16:55,150
An example must be made!

1070
01:16:55,630 --> 01:16:56,990
What do you mean?

1071
01:16:58,070 --> 01:16:59,190
You're fired!

1072
01:16:59,910 --> 01:17:01,910
Is that plain enough for you?

1073
01:17:07,030 --> 01:17:08,390
Oh, buddy!

1074
01:17:09,110 --> 01:17:10,710
And don't call me "buddy"!

1075
01:17:11,470 --> 01:17:15,350
Oh, please, sir! This job running
the elevator, it's all I got!

1076
01:17:15,790 --> 01:17:17,750
It's okay if you don't like the Buzz-Sucker!

1077
01:17:17,830 --> 01:17:20,520
Just let me keep my job,
I'm praying to you!

1078
01:17:21,360 --> 01:17:22,640
Get out of my office!

1079
01:17:23,120 --> 01:17:24,360
Get up! Up!

1080
01:17:25,440 --> 01:17:27,920
We don't crawl here
at Hudsucker Industries!

1081
01:17:29,520 --> 01:17:30,760
I'm sorry, sir!

1082
01:17:30,920 --> 01:17:32,040
I'm sorry!

1083
01:17:45,920 --> 01:17:47,320
Thank you, Aloysius.

1084
01:17:52,240 --> 01:17:53,360
This is...

1085
01:17:55,120 --> 01:17:56,080
...useful.

1086
01:18:13,480 --> 01:18:17,560
I'm sorry I'm late, Sid. That back nine
at Riverdale's really murder.

1087
01:18:18,800 --> 01:18:21,570
It's a tough course. A real lollapalooza.

1088
01:18:23,050 --> 01:18:24,250
Sit down, son.

1089
01:18:27,490 --> 01:18:31,410
I thought the boardroom would be
a swell place to chat undisturbed.

1090
01:18:32,490 --> 01:18:35,730
Seems we've got some security problems
here at the Hud.

1091
01:18:36,810 --> 01:18:37,690
You don't say.

1092
01:18:37,730 --> 01:18:41,890
Ordinarily, I wouldn't bother you with it,
but this is embarrassing.

1093
01:18:43,210 --> 01:18:45,290
It concerns you directly.

1094
01:18:45,610 --> 01:18:48,090
-How's that?
-It's not serious in itself.

1095
01:18:48,730 --> 01:18:51,370
Some elevator boy that you'd fired
came to me...

1096
01:18:51,970 --> 01:18:55,610
...claiming that you'd stolen
the idea for the dingus.

1097
01:18:55,930 --> 01:18:57,530
You'd stolen it from him.

1098
01:19:00,570 --> 01:19:02,890
-Maybe I was a little rough on him...
-Forget it.

1099
01:19:02,970 --> 01:19:06,450
You don't have to explain to me.
He's a little person. He's nothing.

1100
01:19:06,530 --> 01:19:08,010
Fire whoever you want.

1101
01:19:09,930 --> 01:19:11,650
No, the problem is...

1102
01:19:12,290 --> 01:19:13,570
...who you hired.

1103
01:19:14,010 --> 01:19:15,050
That dame.

1104
01:19:15,490 --> 01:19:17,010
A spy, as it turns out.

1105
01:19:17,890 --> 01:19:20,570
She must have gotten
to that elevator schnook...

1106
01:19:21,290 --> 01:19:23,340
...and her paper is going to town.

1107
01:19:24,420 --> 01:19:28,620
Sure, sure, we tried to kill the story,
but the Argus won't play ball.

1108
01:19:30,420 --> 01:19:33,460
The problem the board will have is
you hired this woman...

1109
01:19:33,820 --> 01:19:35,460
...and you kept her on...

1110
01:19:35,780 --> 01:19:38,180
...while she was making
a chump out of you.

1111
01:19:38,740 --> 01:19:40,420
Serious error in judgement.

1112
01:19:41,940 --> 01:19:43,420
Business is war, kid.

1113
01:19:44,500 --> 01:19:46,900
Take no prisoners, give no second chances.

1114
01:19:50,580 --> 01:19:52,940
When the board meets after New Year's...

1115
01:19:53,100 --> 01:19:54,540
...your position....

1116
01:19:57,140 --> 01:19:58,820
Looks like you're finished.

1117
01:19:59,540 --> 01:20:00,580
Washed up.

1118
01:20:06,100 --> 01:20:07,980
Fourteenth hole at Riverdale...

1119
01:20:08,340 --> 01:20:09,860
...some use a mashie...

1120
01:20:10,060 --> 01:20:11,500
...some use a niblick.

1121
01:20:12,460 --> 01:20:13,460
Niblick.

1122
01:20:14,020 --> 01:20:16,180
You get more loft, more backspin.

1123
01:20:20,900 --> 01:20:21,980
That dame...

1124
01:20:23,390 --> 01:20:25,670
...she got your throat pretty well slit.

1125
01:20:26,750 --> 01:20:28,670
When you're dead, you stay dead.

1126
01:20:29,510 --> 01:20:31,870
You don't believe me,
ask Waring Hudsucker.

1127
01:20:34,070 --> 01:20:35,350
Tough luck, kid.

1128
01:20:35,990 --> 01:20:37,630
You had a short climb up.

1129
01:20:38,710 --> 01:20:40,190
It's a long way down.

1130
01:20:52,390 --> 01:20:55,790
-You can't print that!
-We are! She hits the streets tonight.

1131
01:20:56,750 --> 01:20:58,390
And she's dynamite!

1132
01:20:58,470 --> 01:21:02,430
But it's the bunk! Norville showed me his
design for the whatsit the day I met him.

1133
01:21:02,510 --> 01:21:05,190
Buzz couldn't have invented it.
Look at him, he's an imbecile.

1134
01:21:05,270 --> 01:21:09,030
Aren't you a broken record?
Gunderson did design it. He's a prodigy.

1135
01:21:09,150 --> 01:21:11,510
-Says who?
-You're not the only one with sources.

1136
01:21:11,550 --> 01:21:14,070
Smith has a senior source
on the Hud Board. Very senior.

1137
01:21:14,310 --> 01:21:16,430
I bet his initials are Sidney J. Mussburger.

1138
01:21:17,150 --> 01:21:19,710
You lost it. You gone soft,
by the looks of it.

1139
01:21:19,790 --> 01:21:21,310
Soft on the dummy from Dubuque.

1140
01:21:22,310 --> 01:21:23,600
-Muncie.
-Whatever!

1141
01:21:23,680 --> 01:21:27,400
This story's hot and you're no longer
on top of it. It's the scoop of the century!

1142
01:21:27,480 --> 01:21:29,560
The other papers won't have this
till tomorrow!

1143
01:21:29,640 --> 01:21:33,400
Allemeinisher Zeitung, Le Figaro
will be choking on our dust come morning.

1144
01:21:33,440 --> 01:21:36,760
You're fools, both of you!
You're being used, don't you see?

1145
01:21:37,080 --> 01:21:39,880
Take a break. You worked hard on this.
You broke it for us.

1146
01:21:39,960 --> 01:21:42,280
But it's passed you by
and Smith's taking up the slack.

1147
01:21:44,480 --> 01:21:45,760
You want slack...

1148
01:21:46,360 --> 01:21:47,640
...I'll give you slack!

1149
01:21:47,680 --> 01:21:51,960
You're not putting me out to pasture!
I quit! Consider this my resignation!

1150
01:21:53,160 --> 01:21:54,680
Effective immediately!

1151
01:21:57,320 --> 01:21:58,280
Soft.

1152
01:22:07,280 --> 01:22:08,720
So, tell me...

1153
01:22:09,160 --> 01:22:11,680
...why do you feel this woman
betrayed you?

1154
01:22:13,960 --> 01:22:15,480
What's the difference?

1155
01:22:15,520 --> 01:22:18,200
The whole world, it seems, is against you?

1156
01:22:18,280 --> 01:22:19,480
I don't know.

1157
01:22:19,600 --> 01:22:21,280
Und the elevator boy...

1158
01:22:21,400 --> 01:22:24,450
...Buzz, he too works against you?

1159
01:22:26,610 --> 01:22:27,610
Classic.

1160
01:22:27,970 --> 01:22:31,090
Patient displayed listlessness, apathy,
gloomy indifference...

1161
01:22:31,170 --> 01:22:32,930
...und was blue und mopey.

1162
01:22:33,410 --> 01:22:36,890
When asked what the Rorschach stains
represented, patient replied:

1163
01:22:36,970 --> 01:22:40,890
"Nothing much. I don't know.
Just a blotch. Sure beats me".

1164
01:22:41,610 --> 01:22:44,730
Patient shows no ambition,
no get-up-and-go, no vim.

1165
01:22:45,410 --> 01:22:47,610
He is riding the grand loopen-ze-loop...

1166
01:22:47,970 --> 01:22:50,810
...that goes from the height
of delusional gaiety...

1167
01:22:50,890 --> 01:22:52,610
...to the trough of despair.

1168
01:22:53,130 --> 01:22:55,810
He is now near,
but not yet at his lowest point.

1169
01:22:56,170 --> 01:23:00,450
When he reaches bottom, he may erupt
und pose a danger to himself...

1170
01:23:00,650 --> 01:23:01,610
...and others.

1171
01:23:01,810 --> 01:23:03,850
Diagnosis, Dr. Bromfenbrenner?

1172
01:23:04,090 --> 01:23:06,970
Patient is eine manic-depressive paranoid,
type B...

1173
01:23:07,130 --> 01:23:08,850
...with acute schizoid tendencies.

1174
01:23:09,210 --> 01:23:10,890
So, patient is...?

1175
01:23:12,490 --> 01:23:13,530
Precisely.

1176
01:23:14,170 --> 01:23:15,170
Nuts!

1177
01:23:15,610 --> 01:23:16,770
Prescription?

1178
01:23:16,970 --> 01:23:18,850
Three things: Commitment...

1179
01:23:19,410 --> 01:23:21,610
...electroconvulsive therapy...

1180
01:23:21,730 --> 01:23:24,090
...maintenance in eine secure facility.

1181
01:23:39,260 --> 01:23:41,380
Yeah, he's a tall guy. A real mess.

1182
01:23:43,100 --> 01:23:46,540
Look, you better get down here.
He says he's a friend of yours.

1183
01:23:46,700 --> 01:23:49,460
He didn't say.
But, man, is he from Squaresville.

1184
01:23:57,740 --> 01:23:59,060
I want a martini!

1185
01:23:59,660 --> 01:24:01,940
It's New Year's Eve. I deserve a martini.

1186
01:24:02,340 --> 01:24:04,060
It's like I've been telling you...

1187
01:24:04,140 --> 01:24:06,220
I thought you served misfits here!

1188
01:24:06,300 --> 01:24:08,740
That's a roger. But we don't sell alcohol.

1189
01:24:09,180 --> 01:24:11,540
What kind of bar doesn't serve martinis?

1190
01:24:11,780 --> 01:24:15,180
It's a juice-and-coffee bar, man,
like I've been telling you.

1191
01:24:15,380 --> 01:24:17,380
Right. So, I want...

1192
01:24:18,700 --> 01:24:19,820
...a martini.

1193
01:24:20,540 --> 01:24:23,500
I've had a martini in every bar
on the way down here.

1194
01:24:24,060 --> 01:24:26,020
Martinis are for squares, man.

1195
01:24:27,950 --> 01:24:30,630
What'd you call me, you beatnik son of a...

1196
01:24:36,510 --> 01:24:37,830
Look who's here:

1197
01:24:37,950 --> 01:24:39,190
Amy Archer...

1198
01:24:39,470 --> 01:24:41,070
...Prizeter Pule winner.

1199
01:24:41,710 --> 01:24:43,870
Looking for a nitwit to buy you lunch?

1200
01:24:44,790 --> 01:24:46,950
-Bar fella, I'd like...
-I'm sorry.

1201
01:24:47,630 --> 01:24:48,990
...a martini, please.

1202
01:24:49,030 --> 01:24:51,350
I tried to tell you so many times, I....

1203
01:24:52,710 --> 01:24:54,110
It's hard to admit...

1204
01:24:54,150 --> 01:24:55,910
...when you've been wrong.

1205
01:24:56,510 --> 01:24:57,910
If you could just...

1206
01:24:58,310 --> 01:25:00,070
...find it in your heart...

1207
01:25:00,670 --> 01:25:02,470
...to give me another chance.

1208
01:25:04,830 --> 01:25:07,190
"You take no prisoners,
give no second chances".

1209
01:25:07,270 --> 01:25:10,030
Please, Norville!
Please give me one more chance!

1210
01:25:10,750 --> 01:25:12,030
And yourself, too!

1211
01:25:12,190 --> 01:25:13,910
We both deserve one.

1212
01:25:14,150 --> 01:25:17,630
Just give us a second chance.
Together we can fight this thing.

1213
01:25:17,790 --> 01:25:21,750
I know the last story was a lie
and we can prove it. Release a statement!

1214
01:25:21,790 --> 01:25:24,670
-I can help you write it!
-What's the difference?

1215
01:25:25,310 --> 01:25:26,630
I'm all washed up.

1216
01:25:28,040 --> 01:25:28,960
Extinct.

1217
01:25:29,480 --> 01:25:31,480
Homo sapiens sapicus.

1218
01:25:34,280 --> 01:25:36,320
That just about does it.

1219
01:25:37,240 --> 01:25:40,440
I've seen Norville Barnes,
the young man in a big hurry...

1220
01:25:40,880 --> 01:25:44,000
...and I've seen Norville Barnes,
the self-important heel.

1221
01:25:44,320 --> 01:25:47,120
But I've never seen Norville Barnes,
the quitter...

1222
01:25:47,880 --> 01:25:49,440
...and I don't like it.

1223
01:25:51,120 --> 01:25:52,560
